annotation.TEXT: Nope, that's the Green Zone entrance. The Final Zone entrance is down here.
...Video game? ...Nah, that's crazy talk.
Ow, my Triple Play!
...Wait, this isn't the right way. That just leads to a dead end that had a trinket.
...What? Three dimensions? Preposterous!
Hey there, vaunted Info Desk. How's it going?
There's the hub's starting point.
Anyway, let's check out all these checkpoints! As I also showed here on Easy Mode, if you're overlapping two checkpoints at once, the game will rapidly switch between which one is active.
Oh, excellent! Alright, just one more room to go and I'll be out of the Blue Zone!
And now I'm Backstage with Blackstone! ...Oh, wait. That's another thing.
Alright, up here is the way I need to go.
Ow, my plantar fascias!
Well, Viridian's eager to get going, but first, here's a quick look at the map and my stats...
I'm not gonna try to slip by that guy up there again, since I'm not trying for the Purple Zone entrance or anything else around there.
..."We"? Are you the King of All Cosmos?
Wow, awesome! Oh, but if I screw up here, I'll have to repeat that previous room again. Please don't injure Viridian's arches again here or anything like that...

Oh, I just remembered something. Someone pointed out to me in an earlier episode that when I was standing in front of a terminal just right, it looked like Viridian had teeth. Let's see if I can position myself like that in front of this terminal...
Bah! I didn't push right enough there. That checkpoint on the left is going to be a pain to reach, just like the checkpoint on the right was last time on the way forward.
Ow, my The Adventures of Spade Parade!
Well, first, let's check out...
6-room chain
Chain broken!
Come on, I can get through these...
...Whoops! Viridian did it again! I wonder why Viridian sometimes just walks over a gap of that size instead of falling into it like I'd normally expect?
Alright, well, only one death there isn't so bad. But, what about this next room?
Getting past these two squares is surprisingly tricky.
So, next time, the Final Zone! Depending on how well things go, I may or may not decide to split the Final Zone into multiple episodes. We'll see... To be continued...
Ow! Well, I win that bet. But, will the room kill me more times?
If only checkpoints like these existed whilst doing science in other games, such as Super Mario World... Well, I suppose savestates can serve that function, if you're playing on an emulator.
Hmm... Actually, I'm going to go this way.
Also, only 16 deaths today, which all occurred in the Blue Zone. That's really good compared to most of my other Hard Mode episodes!
4-room chain
Yay, trinkets!
Hello, and welcome back to VVVVVV! Let's see how much trouble it'll be for me to get out of the Blue Zone here...
Ow, my chin and tonic!
(Insert evil snicker here.)
Wowsers! I'm on a roll here!
Ow! HM05 Waterfall is incompatible with Viridian. He can't learn Waterfall.
Mmm... Cheese and onion pastie... (*Drools*)
YES!!! And with that, the Blue Zone is now officially complete! Let's take a look at my stats to see how well I'm doing...
Ow, my Math Court!
Yes! But, I still have to get past a couple more spikes to reach the next checkpoint...
There's that "personell" typo again. Should be "personnel".
I was unsure if that "faliure" typo was there on Easy Mode as I was playing this here, but I went back and checked, and it is also misspelled that way on Easy Mode as well.
Ow, my General Mathpital!
Yes, finally! Oh, but I bet the Deathstars in this next room will drive me bananas...
"Tick." Graze +1. It sure looked to me like Viridian's head touched that third disc that time!
I almost had it on that previous one, but I didn't move left in time.
Yeah, I guess going under the floating heart like that works.
Alright, I guess I'm done here. Let's make my way to the entrance of the Final Zone!
Aha, now I can get in! However, we're going to save that for next time!
I'm almost where I want to be...
...There's this failure at spelling "failure" here again.
This is heavy, Doc.
There's that "entirity" typo again. Should be "entirety".
5-room chain
Sweet! Now to struggle with this room for a while... or not!
Actually, it'll be even more of a pain, because I have to fight against the conveyor belts in this room this time.
Alright, here's one more look at the map and my stats... Looks like I've filled out the entire map except for the Final Zone!
Alright, here we go! Hmm... It doesn't look like I can get past these Blu-Ray discs as easily as I did last time...
Ow, my calcaneus! Well, so much for that hot streak.
7-room chain
!sephazon
Ow, my Mega Ring! Now how am I supposed to Mega Evolve my Kangaskhan?
There's that "recieve" typo again. Should be "receive", obviously.
There's that "neccecary" typo again. That is a really bad misspelling of "necessary".
Oh, that's neat. I like how I can just conveniently land in that corner there.
Ah, here we are at the heart room! And, since I have all of the trinkets, the barrier on the right side of the room is now gone!
Ah! There we go! Viridian looks ready to chomp down on stuff now!
Oh, nice! I guess it wasn't quite as much of a pain as I thought it would be, though my experience with reaching the checkpoint on the right last time probably helped there.
!bet 100 red Also, !bet 100 that this room kill me at least once, since it's trickier going back.

Alright, I only died 16 times today on my way out of the Blue Zone, and I've only been playing for about 4 minutes so far, so there's still plenty of time to do the next thing I want to do before heading to the Final Zone!
Mind=blown, again.
Ow, my talus!
"Sephazon is still sleeping. Why are you still using this command, SomeGuy712x?"
